<paragraph id="12C90C5CFC2486CAAAE73E1234EC8838" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="A5FCC6A193DA66641E72D46BA985D6FB" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Panicum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Panicum crus-galli" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crus-galli">
<emphasis id="6A01B03FAFE09034ADD442B9FA9B1EBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Panicum crus-galli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., Sp. Pl. 1: 56. 1753.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="220D69FB88629B55245250C0C4374873" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="5EDAF3EC664DB87FA7178D76A0F20A9C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<typeStatus id="76148215CCDC1EF0EB681ECD8945C9E3">Type</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD79D9D4528327AB3ADDC719E73B86F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Herb. Burser 1: 303, sine dato (UPS).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F11B253724B7C326DFCC6A4D4295D45B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="7DEC2114B581F148038AAA48C7864E07" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91B490620039D4E0C33BBF98ACD2E247" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
There has always been a great deal of confusion about the type; see, e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="0C54BEB8B2D23567927449039A610502" author="Hitchcock, AS" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="113 - 158" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/13772page/148/mode/1up" refId="B29" refString="Hitchcock, AS, 1908. Types of American grasses: A study of the American species of grasses described by Linnaeus, Gronovius, Sloan, Swartz and Michaux. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 12 (3): 113 - 158, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/13772page/148/mode/1up" title="Types of American grasses: A study of the American species of grasses described by Linnaeus, Gronovius, Sloan, Swartz and Michaux." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/13772page/148/mode/1up" volume="12" year="1908">Hitchcock (1908)</bibRefCitation>
or 
<bibRefCitation id="AE91E8FF37D13B369B31F982106DA438" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2423880" author="Gould, FW" journalOrPublisher="American Midland Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="36 - 59" refId="B26" refString="Gould, FW, Ali, MA, Fairbrothers, DE, 1972. A revision of Echinochloa in the United States. American Midland Naturalist 87 (1): 36 - 59, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2423880" title="A revision of Echinochloa in the United States." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2423880" volume="87" year="1972">Gould et al. (1972)</bibRefCitation>
. In fact, all original material came from North America and belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="D17B5E481D6B147B5C1D6357684832C1" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. muricata" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="muricata">
<emphasis id="3AEC8872FD8EA253D4294EB454E8271D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. muricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in 1753 
<taxonomicName id="A3A1026B7E039204E3BEED0AA00B43B2" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. crus-galli" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="crus-galli">
<emphasis id="6BD482C2828380E4D0ACEEAE757DAD9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. crus-galli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from Eurasia, was not yet a widespread introduced species in North America. 
<bibRefCitation id="12DF4DE6AD8F6754E5021CB6C5573D8B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12299" author="Crespo, MB" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="820 - 822" refId="B18" refString="Crespo, MB, Martinez-Azorin, M, Angeles Alonso, M, Pena-Martin, C, 2020b. Proposal to conserve the name Panicum crus-galli (Echinochloa crus-galli) (Poaceae, Panicoideae) with a conserved type. Taxon 69 (4): 820 - 822, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12299" title="Proposal to conserve the name Panicum crus-galli (Echinochloa crus-galli) (Poaceae, Panicoideae) with a conserved type." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12299" volume="69" year="2020 b">Crespo et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
formally proposed to conserve the binomial 
<taxonomicName id="81F4CD03B0291B8715BD7919944BC9F4" genus="P." lsidName="P. crus-galli" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="crus-galli">
<emphasis id="9F566BD3F941A5F1EDBE3DAC87D4C9C9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. crus-galli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a conserved type based on the specimen Herb. Burser I: 103 (UPS), the one previously chosen as 
<normalizedToken id="4CF5FD7EF172EAB8ABF08DDC10D68E69" originalValue="“lectotype”">&quot;lectotype&quot;</normalizedToken>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="B1BCFC76BD498B803D3164AAECC699D9" author="Michael, PW" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Plant Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B50" refString="Michael, PW, 1983. Taxonomy and distribution of Echinochloa species with special reference to their occurrence as weeds of rice. In: International Rice Research Institute (IRRI) and International Weed Science Society (Org.) Proceedings of the Conference on Weed Control in Rice, 31 August-4 September 1981. International Rice Research Institute, Manila, 291-306." title="Taxonomy and distribution of Echinochloa species with special reference to their occurrence as weeds of rice. In: International Rice Research Institute (IRRI) and International Weed Science Society (Org.) Proceedings of the Conference on Weed Control in Rice, 31 August- 4 September 1981. International Rice Research Institute, Manila, 291 - 306." year="1983">Michael (1983)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
